          "summary": "This is the fourth volume in the Architecture of Open Source Applications series, and the first to not feature the words \"open source applications\" anywhere in the title. The first three volumes in the series were about big problems that big programs have to solve. For an engineer who is early in their career, it may be a challenge to understand and build upon programs that are much bigger than a few thousand lines of code, so, while big problems can be interesting to read about, they can also be challenging to learn from.",
